                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d597">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States.</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-05-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 9, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. White states that there is much reason to anticipate an unfavorable report
                    of the committee to Parliament on the meat inspection bill, but statement that
                    such report has been made is premature, and that the Government is exerting
                    itself in behalf of the original bill, which is fairly satisfactory to the
                    Government of the United States. Also that he is shortly to see Minister von
                    Bülow with reference to the subject.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
